title: Measurement of single and double spin-flip probabilities in inelastic deuteron scattering on 12C at 270MeV

probabilities in inelastic deuteron scattering on 12C
at 270MeV

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physics Letters,Section B, Vol.521, Issue.3-4, p.153 (2001)

x4freetext: Beam intensity is 10 nA. (An average current)
POL-BM: The vector and tensor polarizations
with maximum values of (py,pyy)=(0,0), (0,-2),
(2/3,0), and (-1/3,1) were used, the
magnitudes were measured using the d+p elastic
scattering at 270 MeV to be 60 to 70% of the
ideal values.
- Target enrichment is unknown.
- Chemical-form of target is element.
- Physical-form of target is solid.
- Target-thickness is 87.2 mg/cm**2.
- Backing is unknown.
CH2 are used as analyzer target. Deuteron
scattered by carbon and hydrogen show large
angular asymmetries depending, respectively,
on the vector and tensor components.

x4codes.hlp: RIKEN (Inst. of Physical and Chemical Research), Wako, Japan

x4freetext: Ring Cyclotron
SMART spectrometer [T.Ichihara et al., Nucl.
Phys. A569(1994)287c], which had a solid angle
of 5.0 msr and a momentum acceptance of 4
percent
Track reconstruction
Plastic scintillation detectors for triggering
Deuteron polarimetr DPOL, to detect deutron
from the polarized deuteron-Carbon elastic
scattering and pairs of protons produced
through the 1H(polarized deuteron, 2p) reaction
which are used as polarimeter reactions of
deuteron from the primary scattering, and the
calibration of DPOL was done in the energy
range between 230 and 270 MeV [S. Ishida, Ph.D.
thesis, University of Tokyo, 1998
(unpublished)].
